dream: I dreamt that I discovered a dead twin sister which I had no idea about (she doesn't exist in real life). And somehow I knew that she was mute. And I was baffled and shocked and scared and disgusted. I was mad that she copied me and pretended to be me with my friends when I wasn't aware of it. Then i saw a huge crowd of plastic mannequins marching from my right in the fields. I knew I was hallucinating them
interpretation:
In your dream, the discovery of a dead twin sister symbolizes the unexplored or hidden aspects of yourself. This could represent traits, desires, or emotions that you have not yet acknowledged or accepted. The fact that she is mute suggests a lack of communication or expression of these hidden aspects. 

Feeling baffled, shocked, scared, and disgusted signifies your emotional reaction to discovering these suppressed parts of yourself. It may imply a fear of being deceived or betrayed by someone close to you, as you mention being mad that she copied you and pretended to be you with your friends. This could indicate a fear of losing your individuality or being overshadowed by others. 

The appearance of a huge crowd of plastic mannequins marching indicates artificiality and a sense of detachment. This could reflect your perception of the world around you, feeling like people are not genuine or are merely going through the motions without showing their true selves. 

The realization that you are hallucinating these mannequins suggests a possible disconnect from reality or perhaps a questioning of what is real and what is not. This could mirror feelings of confusion or uncertainty in your waking life. Overall, your dream may be signaling a need to explore and integrate hidden aspects of yourself and to assess the authenticity of your relationships.
title: The Secret Sister: Discovering a Silent Doppelgänger Amongst Plastic Hallucinations

dream: I got a call from someone in jail and they went from talkin in English to Spanish . I tried to hang up the call but it would not let me , the phone for ceeh hot and when I threw it I saw a flame of fire but it went away. I picked the phone up and nothin was damaged it just wouldn't come on. But it was still.super hot and kept getting hotter so I dropped it again and the phone broke into pieces. My son picked up the battery and some green wires that was inside of it . Then it went to my son father came to the dream and he had on a white shirt , black and white plaid sweat pants and he had on glasses. He kept trying to come onto me and I remember repeatedly telling him I and that I didn't want anything to do with him .
interpretation:
This dream may symbolize feeling trapped or controlled in a situation in your waking life. The call from someone in jail could represent a sense of being burdened or confined by someone or something. The transition from English to Spanish may suggest a feeling of confusion or difficulty in expressing yourself or understanding the situation.

The overheating and flaming phone could represent the mounting pressure and intensity of the situation. Your attempt to disconnect from it, but being unable to, may reflect a struggle to break free from the perceived constraints. The fact that the phone remained undamaged after being thrown suggests that despite the turmoil, you still have a sense of resilience and strength.

The appearance of your son's father in the dream, along with his attempts to come onto you, may symbolize unresolved issues or tensions from the past. Your rejection of him emphasizes your firm stance in not wanting to engage with him or be involved in anything related to the past.

Overall, the dream seems to indicate a desire for freedom, independence, and protection of personal boundaries in challenging circumstances. It may suggest the need to assert yourself and make choices that prioritize your well-being and emotional security.
title: Incarcerated Multilingual Call, Fiery Consequences, and Unwanted Advances
